## How to Add a New Field to FME Output

### MPAS-O: Add a new derived surface field
1. Add `<var>` to Registry_fme_derived_fields.xml (var_struct + stream)
2. In mpas_ocn_fme_derived_fields.F compute: get from pool, compute, store
3. If remapped output desired: add remap_field + write_var calls

### MPAS-O: Add a new depth-coarsened field
1. Add `<var>` to Registry_fme_depth_coarsening.xml
2. In mpas_ocn_fme_depth_coarsening.F: add to field dispatch logic
   (currently supports temperature, salinity, velocityZonal, velocityMeridional)

### EAM: Add a new derived field
Just add to user_nl_eam: `derived_fld_defs = 'NEW_FIELD=A+B*C'`
No code changes needed — the expression parser handles it dynamically.

### ELM: Add a new source field for vcoarsen
1. In elm_fme_vcoarsen.F90 update routine: add case to select/case block
2. Map the field name to the appropriate ELM data type pointer

